# Parity with `foundation-registry`

This fork tracks `kaelys-js/foundation-registry` for the shared toolchain
(config, qa, sync, mutations) and diverges on top for the `{{fork-product}}`
runtime product. This file records every file that intentionally differs
between the two working trees, and why.

Reference diff command (from either checkout root):

```sh
diff -rq /path/to/foundation-registry /path/to/{{fork-repo}} \
  --exclude=.git --exclude=node_modules --exclude=coverage \
  --exclude=.turbo --exclude=.mise \
  --exclude=packages/products/{{fork-product}} \
  --exclude=.github/workflows/refresh.yml \
  --exclude=.github/workflows/reminders.yml \
  --exclude=.github/workflows/sync-upstream.yml \
  --exclude=.sync-upstream.json
```

## Intentional drifts

### Product set

- `packages/products/{{fork-product}}/` — fork-only. {{fork-product-description}}
- `packages/products/registry/` — upstream-only. Governance records live
  upstream; the fork does not carry them.

### Root-level files

- `TODO.md` — fork's TODO list, scoped to what this fork owns.
- `package.json` — fork's `name`, `description`, and `keywords` reflect the
  fork's actual scope (not the upstream registry).

### Toolchain configs

- `pnpm-lock.yaml` — different transitive graph because the product set
  differs.

### CI + workflows

- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` — byte-identical to upstream. The `validate`
  job self-skips on this fork (no `packages/products/registry/`) via the
  `detect` job's output.
- `.github/workflows/refresh.yml` — fork-only. Nightly refresh of any
  auto-generated docs owned by the fork's product.
- `.github/workflows/reminders.yml` — fork-only. Reminder cadence for the
  fork's product.
- `.github/workflows/sync-upstream.yml` — fork-only. Daily upstream-merge
  workflow with auto-PR + auto-merge fallback. Generated by
  `pnpm sync-upstream:opt-in` from the template in
  `packages/shared/config/workflows/`.

## Remotes on the local fork checkout

- `origin` → `git@github.com:{{fork-owner}}/{{fork-repo}}.git`
- `upstream` → `git@github.com:kaelys-js/foundation-registry.git`

Both remotes assume SSH; a non-interactive session without the key added to
`ssh-agent` will need `GH_TOKEN`-backed HTTPS pushes as a per-session
workaround.
